Package: i386-linux-binutils
Version: 2.19.1
Revision: 1
Architecture: powerpc, i386
Description: GNU binutils for i386-linux
License: LGPL
Maintainer: Karl-Michael Schindler <karl-michael.schindler@web.de>

Source: mirror:gnu:binutils/binutils-%v.tar.bz2
Source-MD5: 09a8c5821a2dfdbb20665bc0bd680791

SourceDirectory: binutils-%v

ConfigureParams: <<
  --target=i386-linux  \
  --prefix=%p/lib/i386-linux \
  --bindir=%p/bin --mandir=%p/share/man --infodir=%p/share/info \
  --program-prefix=i386-linux-
<<

InstallScript: <<
#!/bin/sh -ev
  /usr/bin/make install DESTDIR=%d
  /bin/rm -vrf %i/lib/i386-linux/lib/

  for file_name in %i/share/info/*
  do
    new_file_name=`/bin/echo ${file_name} | /usr/bin/sed -e "s|%i/share/info/|%i/share/info/i386-linux-|g"`
    mv ${file_name} ${new_file_name}
  done
<<

DocFiles: README COPYING*
InfoDocs: i386-linux-as.info i386-linux-bfd.info i386-linux-binutils.info i386-linux-configure.info i386-linux-ld.info i386-linux-standards.info

Homepage: http://www.gnu.org/software/binutils/
DescPort: <<
Like 'avr-binutils' package, lib & include folders have been moved to 
/sw/lib/i386-linux and the binaries are put into /sw/bin .
All xxx files renamed to i386-linux-xxx.info to avoid clashes
with other potential toolchains.
